{
  "texts": [
    "This enables robots to gradually learn to accurately identify and understand different objects in dynamic and diverse interactive environments, just like humans.",
    "Ding et al. (2023) proposed a system called Embodied Concept Learner (ECL), enabling robots to emulate human capabilities in learning visual concepts and understanding geometric mapping within an interactive 3D environment.",
    "The robotic agent, akin to a baby, can acquire longterm, interpretable, unsupervised semantic and depth learning through interactions with humans.",
    "Fig. 8 VLM-based human-guided skill transfer and robot learning.",
    "In learning from human demonstration, purely videobased passive observation may lead robots to struggle to capture the underlying intentions and semantics of actions."
  ]
}